data.title: The Merseybeats, The Merseys and Liverpool Express
data.meta_description: Billy Kinsley of The Merseybeats, The Merseys and Liverpool Express talks about timeless hits and hidden gems. Liverpool
data.text:
Billy Kinsley – The Merseybeats, The Merseys and Liverpool Express

Billy Kinsley of The Merseybeats, The Merseys and Liverpool Express talks about timeless hits and hidden gems.

Liverpool Express – You Are My Love (Single A-side, Warner Bros, 1976)

The Merseybeats – It’s Love That Really Counts (Single A-side, Fontana, 1963)

The Kinsleys – Do Me A Favour (demo) (Unearthed Merseybeat Vol 3, Viper 2005 rec 1964)

The Merseybeats – I Stand Accused (Single A-side, Fontana, 1965)

The Merseys – Sorrow (Single A-side, Fontana, 1966)

The Merseys – So Sad About Us (Single A-side, Fontana, 1966)

Jackie Lomax – New Day (Single A-side, Apple, 1969)

Atlantis – I Ain’t Got Time (Single A-side, Fury, 1972)

Rockin’ Horse – Julian The Hooligan (Yes It Is, Philips, 1971)

Billy Kinsley – Annabella (Single A-side, Epic, 1973)

Liverpool Express – Every Man Must Have A Dream (Single A-side, Warner Bros, 1976)

Liverpool Express – It’s A Beautiful Day (Tracks, Warner Bros, 1976)

Liverpool Express – Dreamin’ (Single A-side, Warner Brothers, 1976)

Liverpool Express – Margie (Dreamin’, Warner Bros – Brazil, 1978)

Liverpool Express – Take It Easy With My Heart (LEX, Warner Bros, 1979)

Liverpool Express – Best Years Of My Life (Once Upon A Time, Every Man, 2003)

Billy Kinsley – Natural High (It’s Love That Really Counts, Cavern City Tours, 2010)

For the first time the three 1970s studio albums by Liverpool Express have been issued on CD by Cherry Red.
